  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Intended use is limited to pre-market submission support for identifying worst-case flow regimes; results must not be extrapolated beyond the 3–6 L/min flow range at 2500–4500 RPM evaluated herein.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cfd-hemolysis-cpb-mrl2",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/fda-gcbp-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-experimental-hemolysis-2019",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-piv-velocity-fields-2020"
  ],
